The paper discusses process modeling and the use of change patterns, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The study conducted in the paper also involves subjective perceptions of process designers, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the need for effective tool support, which could be related to cybernetics (cs.CY).
